John D. Schiller, Jr.

Age : 57Public asset : 33,837 USDLinked companies :  EPL Oil & Gas Inc 





Summary 



Mr. John D. Schiller, Jr., is a Member at American Association of Drilling Engineers, a Member at American Petroleum Institute, Inc., a Member at Houston Producers Forum, a Member at Independent Petroleum Association of America, a Member at Society of Petroleum Engineers, Inc. and Member-Presidents Council at Texas A&M University.He is on the Board of Directors at EPL Oil & Gas, Inc., Particle Drilling Technologies, Inc., Alley Theatre, Energy XXI GOM LLC, Energy XXI Services LLC, Energy XXI Texas Onshore LLC, ESCAPE Family Resource Center, M21K LLC and The National Ocean Industries Association. Mr. Schiller was previously employed as President, Chief Executive Officer & Director by Energy XXI (Bermuda) Ltd., Vice President-Exploration & Production by Devon Energy Corp., Executive Vice President-Exploration & Production by Ocean Energy, Inc. /Old/, Senior Vice President-Operations by Seagull Energy Corp., Manager-Corporate Acquisitions by Burlington Resources, Inc., Staff Engineer by Superior Oil & Gas Co., President, Chief Executive Officer & Director by Energy XXI Gulf Coast, Inc., a Trustee by Houston Ballet Foundation, and Chairman by Texas A&M Department of Petroleum Engineering.He received his undergraduate degree from Texas A&M University.



